items.Video_Title: Crochet Skirt - In-depth Tutorial for Beginners
items.Video_Description:
💞 Welcome to another In-depth Crochet Tutorial from ABoC Studio!💞

This Crochet Thigh-laced Skirt is an original ABoC Studio's design. The pattern was written with love & care by me, Natalie. Feel free to share the pattern, and sell your final hand-crafted product. In all cases, make sure you credit ABoC Studio. Thank you 🤍

WHAT YOU NEED:

1. Crochet Hook: 6.00mm and 5.0mm (you’ll need both)

2. Yarn 125-250gr (depends on how big your skirt is; usually I wear S-XS so my skirt is 125gr). Any Yarn from category No.2/Fine or No.3/Dk or No.4/Aran would work (The thinner the yarn the lacier the fabric would turn out; in this video I used 2 types of yarn: Purple acrylic No.3/Dk and a little bit of Orange mohair No.1/Fingering). Mohair works great with this pattern. However, mohair and dark color yarn are only recommended for advanced crocheters (Because they’re quite hard to handle) 🧶🧶🧶

• Scissors and Yarn Needle

• Waist & Hip Measurements: This is a made-to-measure pattern, so if you’re about to make this skirt for yourself then these measurements are not necessary. We can just try the chain on our bodies.


PATTERN NOTE

We’re gonna start at the waist with a chain that is based on the Hip-measurement (The waist is usually smaller than the hip, so the skirt’s waist-line always needs to be big enough to slide through our hips).

We need to use a bigger hook (6.0mm) to work the chain before switching to the smaller one (5.0mm) for the rest of the skirt. This is because we don’t want our chain line to be stiff, and using bigger hook kinda adds a bit of stretch and makes it go easier.

This is a "made-to-measure" pattern, there will be NO given number of chains & stitches.  I recommend you to keep counting these numbers on the piece you work on, so that the shape of your skirt would be nice & even.
